        "textSnippet": "Dino's\nClosed · opens tomorrow at 4pm\nHome\nMenu Highlights\nHours & Location\nContact\nCall Now\nAbout Dino's\n\nA family-run neighborhood pizza and pasta shop with takeout, delivery, dine-in beer, and enough menu depth to keep regulars rotating back.\n\n1997\nSnippet-sourced start year\n4.5\nVisible Google rating at capture\n252\nVisible Google reviews at capture\n4 PM\nTypical opening time\n\nDino's official about page says the shop is a small family owned and operated restaurant in old town Lake in the Hills. Search and snippet evidence also frames the business as family owned and operated since 1997.\n\nThe official menu is the real sales asset: crispy thin crust made from scratch daily, double dough, old fashioned in-the-pan pizza, stuffed Chicago-style deep dish, gluten-free crust, pasta dinners, sandwiches on garlic bread, and a bar setup built around beer and game-on-TV energy.\n\nThe current official homepage does not package any of that clearly. This preview fixes the first impression by leading with the pizza formats, the call-first path, the hours, and the menu proof people actually need.\n\nDino's\n6 Miller Rd\nLake in the Hills, IL 60156\n(847) 658-3300\ndinospizza64@gmail.com\nMonday: Closed\nTuesday: Closed\nWednesday: 4 PM - 9 PM\nThursday: 4 PM - 9 PM\nFriday: 4 PM - 10 PM\nSaturday: 4 PM - 10 PM\nSunday: 4 PM - 9 PM\nVisit\nMenu Highlights\nHours & Location\nAbout\nContact\nConversion\nCall Now\nOffi"
